issue.title: Add decoration to tracks in track listing to mark overall status

milestone.title: Complete checkup process
milestone.description: The checkup process is the user flow of selecting a track, completing questions, submitting the responses, and viewing related statistics.

issue.body:
Aside from a percentage, we should add a ribbon or some mark to distinguish completed tracks from new, untouched, or pending tracks.

Statuses:

- New: if we add timestamps for when a track is created, then we can mark it as new if that timestamp falls within a designated period (e.g. 2 weeks from creation is marked as new for returning users). This mark may coexist with the 'not started' mark.
- Untouched (not started): the user did not start the track at all.
- Pending: the user started the track, but has not completed it.
- Submit: the user's submission failed, and they must resubmit to complete the track.
- Completed: the user completed the track and submitted their responses.
